---

<DocsLayout title="Card" description="A container component for grouping related content with consistent styling" activeComponent="card">
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-pretty">Card</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">A container component for grouping related content with consistent styling.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mw-separator"></div>

    <!-- Preview -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Preview</h2>
      <div class="mw-card">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <!-- Profile Card -->
          <div class="mw-card">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="mw-avatar">
                <span>AJ</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold">Alice Johnson</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Product Designer</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-3 leading-relaxed">
              Passionate about creating intuitive user experiences that solve real problems.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Notification Card -->
          <div class="mw-card">
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
              <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
                <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold">New comment on your post</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1">2 minutes ago</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-2">
                  "Great insights! I'd love to hear more about your approach."
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Pricing Card -->
          <div class="mw-card">
            <div class="text-center">
              <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Pro</h3>
              <div class="mt-2">
                <span class="text-3xl font-bold">$29</span>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">/mo</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-primary" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
                Unlimited projects
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-primary" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
                Advanced analytics
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-primary" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
                Priority support
              </li>
            </ul>
            <button class="mw-btn mw-btn-primary w-full mt-4">Get started</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Code Examples -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Code</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Profile Card</p>
          <CodeBlock code={profileCardCode} lang="html" />
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Notification Card</p>
          <CodeBlock code={notificationCardCode} lang="html" />
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pricing Card</p>
          <CodeBlock code={pricingCardCode} lang="html" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Usage -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Usage</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">CSS Classes</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-2">
            The <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">mw-card</code> class provides the base card styling with background, border, border radius, padding, and shadow. All styling is controlled through your <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">marrow.config.js</code> theme configuration.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Layout Patterns</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-2">
            Cards can be composed with any content structure. Common patterns include header sections with titles, content areas with text or images, and footer sections with actions. Use standard Tailwind utilities for internal spacing and layout.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Grid Layouts</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-2">
            Cards work well in responsive grid layouts using Tailwind's grid utilities: <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4</code>. Adjust column counts and gaps based on your design needs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Accessibility</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-2">
            Cards are primarily visual containers and don't require specific ARIA roles. If a card is interactive (clickable), ensure it uses a semantic element like <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">&lt;a&gt;</code> or <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">&lt;button&gt;</code> with appropriate focus styles. Add <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">aria-hidden="true"</code> to decorative icons.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
